title: The Beginning
author: Itaqi
pages:
#- 




             Orion
      The Beginning
#- 

For Arthreas: May his return be glorious and infinite







#- Chapter 1: Land Grab

As a founder of Orion, I was given the task to find a suitable location for Orion. I thought that the best way to do that was to visit the already established Eslenti and Ulaan Baatar.

My first visit was to
#- Eslenti. I got there, after some troubles (I mixed up my coordinates.. -_-), I made it there and was greeted by belthazor, JM120897, and Puig19. They gave me some food in exchange for some Iron armor I found in an NPC village. I felt that the area around 
#- Eslenti was not so good to make a town, as it was on a beach (poor planning on belthazor's part). I left there to head to Ulaan Baatar, the city you know as Harvest.

At Ulaan Baatar, I looked around for a bit and asked wadefrakers if there was a forest 
#-  nearby. No one seemed to have found the large forest 400 blocks south. I set out to look for one and found it within 15 minutes.

I, being a bit hasty, claimed that land for Orion, originally claiming a 400m radius from -4550, -5555. Myself and 555NY dug
#- a hole in the area under the current capitol building. The name "Temp base" came from my laziness to write out "Temporary" on the snitch. That snitch has been there since May, and will remain there for as long Orion stands.

Seldomshock showed
#- up a bit late, as he had issues with the queue. I did all the beginning work, and most of what was seldomshock's term as president while he was off "traveling".

All that was done was the tempbase and Hunter's Bridge.
#- Chapter 2: Rapid Growth

As we gained newly-spawned players, our population skyrocketed from 3 to around 35 in 5 days. Some of these players you will still see today, while some have moved, others stayed:

